scenes.title: truncated dodecahedron (90b1)
scenes.content: Build a truncated dodecahedron (edge length b1).

scenes.title: base red (3b1)
scenes.content: Rotate the truncated dodecahedron so that a triangular face is horizontal. Lay the base of a first extended prism, a triangle with edge length b1, just ABOVE the bottom triangle of the truncated dodecahedron, rotated by about 30°.

scenes.title: side edges red (12y1 3y3)
scenes.content: Insert (preferably vertically) the three side edges of the first extended prism (edge length y1+y1+y3+y1+y1). The upper ends of these side edges lie just UNDERNEAT the top triangle of the truncated dodecahedron.

scenes.title: prism red (9b1)
scenes.content: Connect these ends by b1 struts, forming the second base of the first extended prism, rotated by about 30° with respect to the top triangle of the truncated dodecahedron. Also connect the vertices in between y1 and y3 struts by b1 struts, forming two triangles (the bases of the first prism of the final model).That way, this first extended prism (like all subsequent ones) is squeezed in between two triangular faces of the truncated dodecahedron, so that the whole structure stays together during buildup, and one has both hands free to insert new elements.

scenes.title: base black (3b1)
scenes.content: Lay the base of extended prism 2 just ABOVE a triangle of the truncated dodecahedron, rotated by about 30°.

scenes.title: side edges black (12y1 3y3)
scenes.content: Insert the three side edges of extended prism 2.

scenes.title: prism black (9b1)
scenes.content: Connect the free ends of these side edges by b1 struts, forming the second base of extended prism 2, just underneath another triangle of the truncated dodecahedron, rotated by about 30°. Also connect the vertices in between y1 and y3 struts by b1 struts, forming the bases of prism 2 in the final model.

scenes.title: truncated dodecahedron removed
scenes.content: Remove the truncated dodecahedron. Probably the truncated dodecahedron will be broken at some point(s), due to increasing tension, after insertion of the penultimate and last extended prisms. No worries, by then the structure is stable enough by itself.

scenes.title: prism extensions removed
scenes.content: Remove the bases and y1 struts of all extended prisms. This way one easily obtains, without dexterity issues, "one of the most frustrating models" George Hart ever made (back in 2001).
